Example issues artifact:

```json
{
  "status": "issues_found",
  "summary": "The feature works in the happy path, but error handling and regression coverage are incomplete.",
  "issues": [
    {
      "path": "ralph/pipeline/runner.py",
      "severity": "high",
      "summary": "A failure path still treats runtime text as markup."
    }
  ],
  "what_came_up_short": [
    "`ralph/pipeline/runner.py` still has one failure output path that renders runtime text unsafely.",
    "There is no regression test proving malformed tool payloads cannot crash the remaining CLI error output path."
  ],
  "how_to_fix": [
    "Convert the remaining CLI failure output path to a Rich `Text`-based render so runtime strings are always treated as literal text.",
    "Add a regression test that feeds bracket-heavy runtime text through the affected path and confirms rendering does not raise `MarkupError`."
  ]
}
```
